{"data":{"post":{"id":"cG9zdDo2MDk1","excerpt":"<p>Jobs to be Done is a way of thinking about products and services. Using JTBD as a way of thinking brings a different perspective that helps us: Avoid building things &#8230; </p>\n<div><a href=\"/jtbd-jobs-to-be-done-an-intro/\" class=\"more-link\">Read More</a></div>\n","content":"\n<p>Jobs to be Done is a way of thinking about products and services. Using JTBD as a way of thinking brings a different perspective that helps us:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Avoid building things that no one wants.</li><li>Understand at a deeper level what a product needs to do</li><li>Reveal why and how people choose a product or service</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s a useful &#8220;Framing&#8221; of the problem space, and way to &#8220;Focus&#8221; what we do and how we learn about what we do.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1750\" height=\"1164\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1750,h_1164/v1613032041/W/image-1_603494b82/image-1_603494b82.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6034\" srcset=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/v1613032041/W/image-1_603494b82/image-1_603494b82.png 1750w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_300,h_200,c_scale/v1613032041/W/image-1_603494b82/image-1-300x200.png 300w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1024,h_681,c_scale/v1613032041/W/image-1_603494b82/image-1-1024x681.png 1024w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_768,h_511,c_scale/v1613032041/W/image-1_603494b82/image-1-768x511.png 768w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1536,h_1022,c_scale/v1613032041/W/image-1_603494b82/image-1-1536x1022.png 1536w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_100,h_67,c_scale/v1613032041/W/image-1_603494b82/image-1-100x67.png 100w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1170,h_778,c_scale/v1613032041/W/image-1_603494b82/image-1-1170x778.png 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1750px) 100vw, 1750px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine you’re a Product Manager and while having a shower you have a genius idea for a new product. What is the probability/likelihood of that idea becoming a successful product?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Well, <a href=\"https://www.questia.com/library/journal/1P3-11645200/3-000-raw-ideas-equals-1-commercial-success\">a study in 1997 by Stevens and Burley</a> looked at project literature, patent literature/experience, and data from venture capital. Their research reported that the ratio was between 0.008% (Low estimate) up to 0.059% (High Estimate). It’s of course different for different industries. For pharmaceuticals, it’s as high as 9000:1. For mature companies launching additional adjacent products (e.g. extending a product line), it’s a bit lower, but the middle ground, looking across different industries was 0.033%: 1 in 3000.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1406\" height=\"1052\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1406,h_1052/v1613421776/W/image-2_6035344b6/image-2_6035344b6.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6035\" srcset=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/v1613421776/W/image-2_6035344b6/image-2_6035344b6.png 1406w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_300,h_224,c_scale/v1613421776/W/image-2_6035344b6/image-2-300x224.png 300w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1024,h_766,c_scale/v1613421776/W/image-2_6035344b6/image-2-1024x766.png 1024w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_768,h_575,c_scale/v1613421776/W/image-2_6035344b6/image-2-768x575.png 768w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_100,h_75,c_scale/v1613421776/W/image-2_6035344b6/image-2-100x75.png 100w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1170,h_875,c_scale/v1613421776/W/image-2_6035344b6/image-2-1170x875.png 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1406px) 100vw, 1406px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>What we envisage looks like this. You’ve lined it all up, built it, done all the work. And you’re excited about launching. It’s gonna be great!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1354\" height=\"902\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1354,h_902/v1613421667/W/image-3/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6037\" srcset=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/v1613421667/W/image-3/image-3.png 1354w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_300,h_200,c_scale/v1613421667/W/image-3/image-3-300x200.png 300w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1024,h_682,c_scale/v1613421667/W/image-3/image-3-1024x682.png 1024w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_768,h_512,c_scale/v1613421667/W/image-3/image-3-768x512.png 768w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_100,h_67,c_scale/v1613421667/W/image-3/image-3-100x67.png 100w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1170,h_779,c_scale/v1613421667/W/image-3/image-3-1170x779.png 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1354px) 100vw, 1354px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ve done all the thinking. You&#8217;re hoping for a nice, smooth launch, popular product, that everyone loves. You hit go, and…</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_588,h_331/v1613421794/W/epic-fail/epic-fail.gif\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6038\" width=\"588\" height=\"331\" /></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p>Not quite what you were hoping for. Products that don’t satisfy the JTBD go a bit like this. &#8220;Agile&#8221; and &#8220;Lean Startup&#8221; might help you get here more quickly, but they can’t tell you <em>why</em> it didn’t go well.JTBD at least gives you some theory and insight into why.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most of us probably aren&#8217;t working on brand new products though. More likely we are working on making improvements to existing products, right? What does Jobs To Be Done have for us? Well, quite a lot, actually. The reason is that there is a second category of product failure that Jobs To Be Done can help us avoid. Disruption.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Disruption of course has become one of those buzzwords that&#8217;s become so overused that it&#8217;s almost meaningless, but back when Clayton Christensen wrote &#8220;The Innovator&#8217;s Dilemma&#8221; it actually meant something quite specific. Something that is relevant for those of us seeking to improve our products. It was rooted in &#8220;over serving&#8221; the Job To Be Done. The gif form of over serving looks a bit like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6043\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Ouch.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>An example might help in understanding JTBD</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Advanced Photo System, or &#8220;APS&#8221;, is one of my favourite examples of &#8220;overserving&#8221;. Launched in 1996, Kodak listened to its customers and gave them a bunch of things they wanted, improving existing parameters of performance a number of ways:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>New features, like <strong>High Def.</strong> and <strong>Panoramic shots</strong>.</li><li>An <strong>easier way to load</strong> film.&nbsp;</li><li>A more compact and secure way of <strong>storing negatives</strong>.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1478\" height=\"1114\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1478,h_1114/v1613032076/W/image-4/image-4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-6045\" srcset=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/v1613032076/W/image-4/image-4.png 1478w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_300,h_226,c_scale/v1613032076/W/image-4/image-4-300x226.png 300w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1024,h_772,c_scale/v1613032076/W/image-4/image-4-1024x772.png 1024w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_768,h_579,c_scale/v1613032076/W/image-4/image-4-768x579.png 768w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_100,h_75,c_scale/v1613032076/W/image-4/image-4-100x75.png 100w, https://res.cloudinary.com/blackswanfarming/images/f_auto,q_auto/w_1170,h_882,c_scale/v1613032076/W/image-4/image-4-1170x882.png 1170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1478px) 100vw, 1478px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>APS was an attempt at a major upgrade of photographic technology aimed at amateurs, giving them professional features and taking away a bunch of easily observed pain points.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But of course, in only a few short years APS was dead, completely overtaken by an <em>initially inferior </em>product: Digital Photography. It&#8217;s the fact that the new technology is initially inferior that makes it what Christensen termed &#8220;disruptive innovation&#8221;.</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" />\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><a href=\"Focus on the higher purpose\">Next: JTBD Lesson #1: Focus on the higher purpose</a></p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" />\n\n\n\n<p>Want more on JTBD? Here&#8217;s 5 lessons you can get from Jobs to be Done (JTBD):</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p><a href=\"/jtbd-lesson-1-focus-on-the-higher-purpose/\">JTBD Lesson #1: Focus on the higher purpose</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"/jtbd-lesson-2-the-jtbd-doesnt-change-the-product-we-hire-does/\">JTBD Lesson #2: The JTBD doesn’t change. The product we hire does.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>JTBD Lesson #3: Beware of Overserving</p>\n\n\n\n<p>JTBD Lesson #4: Segment by JTBD</p>\n\n\n\n<p>JTBD Lesson #5: </p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>(Above will get updated with links as they are published!)</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\" />\n\n\n\n<p>Previous Posts on Jobs to be Done:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"/health-tracking-jobs-to-be-done/\">Health Tracking Jobs to be Done</a></p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n","title":"JTBD (Jobs To Be Done) – An Intro","date":"May 16, 2020","featuredImage":{"node":{"altText":"","localFile":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='400'%20height='266'%20viewBox='0%200%20400%20266'%20preserveAspectRatio='none'%3e%3cpath%20d='M0%2060v206h401V0H0v60m184-18c-1%202-1%203-3%203-4%200-4%201-1%203%202%201%202%202%201%204-2%203-1%204%202%201%203-1%203-1%205%201s3%201%202-2c-1-2%200-3%202-5l3-2h-4c-2%200-3-1-4-3l-2-3-1%203M54%2064c-6%200-6%200-6%203%200%202%200%202%204%202h4v43l2%201c5%201%205%200%205-23V69h4c4%200%204%200%204-3-1-3-3-3-17-2m21%2024v25h9c11-1%2012-2%2015-6%204-6%202-17-3-20-1-1-1-1%201-3%204-4%204-13%200-17-3-3-8-4-16-4h-6v25m31-24v25l1%2023h8c15%200%2017-3%2017-24s-2-23-17-24h-9M36%2085c0%2022%200%2023-5%2023-1%200-2%201-2%203s0%202%204%202c9%200%2010-2%2010-28V64h-7v21m47-9c0%207%201%208%205%207%203%200%205-3%205-7s-1-6-6-7h-4v7m31%2012v19h3c7%200%209-5%208-25-1-12-2-13-8-13h-3v19M83%2098v9h3c6%200%207-2%207-8%201-7-1-9-6-10h-4v9m101%202c-1%202-2%203-4%203h-2l2%202c2%202%202%202%201%204-2%203-1%204%202%202l3-2%202%202c3%202%204%201%202-2-1-1%200-2%201-4l2-1-2-1-4-3c-1-3-2-3-3%200M20%20132l2%209c2%2011%203%2012%205%202l2-5%201%206%202%206c2-1%205-19%204-20s-2%201-3%205c0%206-2%206-2%200-2-7-5-6-5%202l-1%202-1-2c0-4-1-7-3-7l-1%202m55-1l-1%203-1%201-1%202h-1c-1-2-5-3-7-1l-1%207c0%205%201%207%204%207s5-3%205-8l1-4%201%206c0%205%200%206%202%206